headline: Stocks to Watch Recap: Hasbro, Circle, Amazon, Nintendo
summary: ↗️ Hasbro (HAS): The toy maker laid off 3% of its workforce, amounting to about 150 employees, as part of a multi-year restructuring. The maker of Monopoly board games and Nerf blasters warned in April that tariffs could ultimately lead to layoffs.
